    "texto": "Honesty is all I've got,\" she said finally, speaking in a low voice. \"I don't have family. I don't have beauty, or a man. I don't have money, and I sure as hell don't have a future. All I've got to prop up my pride is my word.\" Her chin rose. \"When Jenny Jones says something, you can bet your last peso that it's true.",
